{"body": "IMHO, the only commands we need inside an engine's project are _generate_ and _console_, as @josevalim already pointed out.\n_rails/commands_ is pretty hard to extend to achieve this behavior.\nWhat do you think about introducing _rails/engine/commands_ that handles the commands that are needed by engines only?\nThis solution separates application's and engine's command line processing.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1242245", "created_at": "2011-05-26T13:27:47Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1327#issuecomment-1242245", "updated_at": "2011-05-26T13:28:23Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1327, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/flippingbits", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/58fd9abfc19da9b36f48ac3454bbad7e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F209938e990dd8b13c4691e30ef6af31f.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/received_events", "gravatar_id": "58fd9abfc19da9b36f48ac3454bbad7e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "flippingbits", "type": "User", "id": 128683, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/flippingbits/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238597ebd3543c151011d08"}, "id": 1242245, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1327"}
